channel.title: Error connecting to wrong ip?
channel.description: When I try to login it, I can sightly see what it says and it says "10 on port 43594" for a sec then going to error connecting.. I.. At first it was port 5555 I changed it to 43594 to see if it would work, but it still didn't.. My ip is under localhost.. It did not change the ip to localhost, but 10.. Why is that? Yes I compiled.. Many of times.. >,>

item.title: Error connecting to wrong ip?
item.dc:creator: @PK_Syndicate PK Syndicate
item.description:
@PK_Syndicate wrote:

If the ip is still “10” and you have set it as localhost, then it is either not reading from the ip String when it says “10” or it’s not compiling the class as you think it is. Use an IDE to compile.
